text.section:
One (1) or more foreign corporations may merge or enter into a share exchange with one (1) or more domestic corporations if:
In a merger, the merger is permitted by the law of the state or country under whose law each foreign corporation is incorporated and each foreign corporation complies with that law in effecting the merger;
In a share exchange, the corporation whose shares will be acquired is a domestic corporation, whether or not a share exchange is permitted by the law of the state or country under whose law the acquiring corporation is incorporated;
The foreign corporation complies with KRS 271B.11-050 if it is the surviving corporation of the merger or acquiring corporation of the share exchange; and
Each domestic corporation complies with the applicable provisions of KRS 271B.11-010 to 271B.11-040 and, if it is the surviving corporation of the merger or acquiring corporation of the share exchange, with KRS 271B.11-050.
